<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="45" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d45">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to Prime Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d45fn1">Sent to the White House Map Room; forwarded to
                                the United States Naval Attaché, London, via Navy
                            channels.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hyde
                                        Park</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-01">1 September 1944</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Number 614, personal and top secret, from the President to the Prime
                            Minister.</p>
                        <p>So happy your temperature is normal but this is the time to go slow.
                            Remember I am entirely free and can go to <gloss target="#t_Octagon1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Octagon</hi></gloss> literally any time if
                            the doctors suggest a postponement for a week or several weeks. I
                            suggest you make Clemmie<note n="2" xml:id="d45fn2">Mrs.
                                Churchill.</note> the arbiter. The armies keep rolling along and a
                            few weeks of delay on our part will not slow them up.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>